quest_title: If n(U) = 20, n(A) = 10 and n(B) = 15, the minimum value of \(n(A \cap B) \) is:
explanation_txt:
NOTE THIS:

  • condition of maximum intersection = condition of minimum union, when one set is proper subset of other
  • condition of minimum intersection = condition of maximum union, when two sets are disjoint

According to this, the minimum value of \(n(A \cap B) \) is 0. But, this gives the maximum value of \(n(A \cup B) = 25\) which is not possible because the universal set has only 20 elements. Actually, the maximum value of \(n(A \cup B)\) is only 20.Hence there should be at least 5 elements in the intersection.
